The paper proposes a formal semantics for a language used to state conditions for accessing resources, which falls under the domain of programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also addresses the issue of interpretation in agreements, which is related to security and cryptography (cs.CR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper uses formal methods to determine when a permission is implied, which falls under the domain of logic in computer science (cs.LO). Finally, the paper proposes a tractable fragment of the language, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE).
